ğŸ’¾ Practical Example â€“ File Download (TCP)

When downloading a file:

Every packet must be correct

Even one missing packet corrupts the file

â†’ Thatâ€™s why TCP is used.

Speed is less important than accuracy.

âš  Why Not Use UDP for Everything?

Because some things must be accurate, like:

Money transfers

Banking transactions

Password authentication

API requests

You cannot afford missing or out-of-order packets.

â­ Summary in One Line
TCP = Reliable but slower
UDP = Faster but unreliable

Both are essential depending on the situation.
